#!N 
#!N  #!Rtall206 Data 
Component #!N #!N #!N The "data" component stores the user's data 
values. The data values can be position- or connection-dependent, as specified 
by the value of the "dep" attribute (described in  #!Lsca,dxall223 h Standard Attributes  #!EL  ) 
of the "data" component. If the values are position-dependent, then the 
"connections" component supplies a means of interpolating data values between the 
samples. If the values are connection-dependent, the data value is constant 
for each interpolation element. Data can also be dependent on "faces" 
or "polylines" (see  #!Legnpols,dxall221 h Edges and Polylines  #!EL  ), in which case the data is 
constant for either the face or the polyline. #!N #!N The 
data are in one-to-one correspondence with the component upon which they 
are dependent. This means that they are specified in the same 
order as the items in the corresponding component. If that component 
is specified in a compact form, its contents are ordered as 
described in  #!Larrays,dxall252 h Arrays  #!EL  . #!N #!N #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   Next Topic #!EF 
#!N #!N  #!Lcolcom,dxall207 h Colors, Front Colors, and Back Colors Components  #!EL  #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   #!N 
